    - type: text
      text: "Looking at the latest 3 commits on the current branch `lgq/wechat-ai-partner`, dated 2026-04-03, the core new feature is in the 3rd commit while the first two are primarily merge operations.\n\n1. `79b85bc6ad` `Merge remote-tracking branch 'origin/main' into feature/0326-boss`\nSyncs the latest `origin/main` content into the current feature branch. The main changes brought in are:\n- On the `meeting` side, the `signature_quote` speaker recognition changes\n- `packages-pc/hddr/src/claw` brought in a batch of frontend changes, focusing on desktop onboarding, layout/UI adjustments, chat page refinements, routing and analytics additions, plus some debug/console cleanup\n\n2. `15719566ea` `Merge branch 'fix/c0304' into 'main'`\nThis is a merge commit bringing `fix/c0304` into `main`. It doesn't introduce new logic itself; its main purpose is to officially merge the `feat(meeting)` commit below into the main branch.\n\n3. `ea8aa3bf52` `feat(meeting): C04 add signature quote field for speaker recognition signature_quote`\nThis is the most substantive feature commit among the three. Key changes:\n- Added `signature_quote` field to meeting C04 speaker recognition results to store representative quotes\n- Updated LLM output format, normalize logic, and prompt to require more specific business terms and verbatim quotes\n- Adjusted display logic to combine `signal_summary + signature_quote` for presentation\n- Added `signature_quote` to the person binding callback payload\n- Added corresponding unit tests and integration tests\n\nIn summary: the main thread of these three commits is adding a representative quote field to meeting speaker recognition, merging that capability into `main`, then syncing it back to your current branch -- along with a batch of `claw` frontend onboarding and UI cleanup changes.\n\nIf you'd like, I can further break down the frontend changes in the first merge commit into specific pages/interactions that were modified."
